  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This package documents the credibility assessment for a CFD-based hemolysis prediction model applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass conditions. The model has been applied in clinical research settings to identify worst-case hemolysis operating points for Class II CPB devices at Model Risk Level 2. A full 13-factor ASME V&V 40 assessment was performed: 7 factors were formally assessed (all meeting required levels), and 6 factors were scoped out as acceptable at MRL 2. This submission conforms to the Minimal profile and does not include a structured Context of Use object; intended-use scope is conveyed through narrative description only.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-fda-centrifugal-pump-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-cpb-boundary-conditions-v2"
  ],
